            "description":"This map is an ongoing project loosely inspired by the architecture of German Renaissance castle.",
            "license":"unknown",
            "releasenotes": "This map is an ongoing project loosely inspired by the architecture of German Renaissance castle, Wewelsburg, located in the village of Wewelsburg, which is a district of the town of Büren, Westphalia, in the Landkreis of Paderborn in the northeast of North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. The castle walls bear a rich occult history filled with many mysteries and centuries old horrors portrayed throughout this build.\n\nCreator - ThorMode9",
